---
description: PHP security rules — escaping, hashing, prepared statements, input validation
globs: **/*.php
alwaysApply: false
---

Security rules:

Escape all user-provided content in views using htmlspecialchars.

Passwords must be hashed using password_hash.

Never store plain text passwords.

Validate all user input server-side.

Use prepared statements for all SQL queries.

Reject uploads that are not valid image files.

Never trust data coming from superglobals ($_GET, $_POST, $_FILES, etc).

Always validate input before use.
